js.unisa.edu.au/index.php/jps/article/view/1269\">\"Open thinking, closed questioning: Two kinds of open and closed question\"</a>. <i>Journal of Philosophy in Schools</i>. <b>2</b> (2). <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.21913/JPS.v2i2.1269\">10.21913/JPS.v2i2.1269</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number\" title=\"International Standard Serial Number\">ISSN</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.worldcat.org/issn/2204-2482\">2204-2482</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Philosophy+in+Schools&amp;rft.atitle=Open+thinking%2C+closed+questioning%3A+Two+kinds+of+open+and+closed+question&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.date=2015-11-29&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.21913%2FJPS.v2i2.1269&amp;rft.issn=2204-2482&amp;rft.aulast=Worley&amp;rft.aufirst=Peter&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ojs.unisa.edu.au%2Findex.php%2Fjps%2Farticle%2Fview%2F1269&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AClosed-ended+question\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation journal\">Howard Schuman &amp; Stanley Presser (October 1979). \"The Open and Closed Question\". <i>American Sociological Review</i>. <b>44</b> (5): 692\u2013712. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.2307/2094521\">10.2307/2094521</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/2094521\">2094521</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=American+Sociological+Review&amp;rft.atit